While we&#39;ll continue to make small fixes to the Heritrix 1.14.X line, 
all major new features will only appear in Heritrix 3.0.X and higher.

Also, because of a number of changes and refactorings (including the 
adoption of the Spring framework for configuring crawls), it&#39;s generally 
easier to customize and extend the H3 codebase.

So while both are fine if they work for your other purposes, the kinds 
of people writing their own extension classes are also most likely to 
prefer H3, for both its architecture and the longevity of their code.

More info is available on the project wiki pages about Heritrix 3:

https://webarchive.jira.com/wiki/display/Heritrix/Heritrix3

- Gordon @ IA

